json.caption:
Some sculptures from my design workshops, and other places.

It‚Äôs been over 6 years since I left a pretty good gig at one of the biggest game companies in the world, to do stuff like this. To sculpt and teach and develop my own projects. It has not been easy. Not in any way shape or form. But it has been worth it.

I‚Äôve met a ton of great people. Many of the brilliant students and artists I‚Äôve worked with have become my friends and collaborators. It‚Äôs so cool. I can‚Äôt believe it sometimes. I think staying at the big company might have been the smarter thing to do. For sure it would have been safer. But it wouldn‚Äôt have been right. I believe that deep in my core, and every once in a while I have to remind myself to take a look around at my life. At how I spend my time, and the relationship I have with my son because I chose this path. I have to give thanks everyday because although I DO absolutely work my tail off, I‚Äôm not sure I‚Äôve earned this.
Thank you all for your interest in my work and for your support. Much love and Happy New Year!

In other news, there are some significant items worth mentioning here at the start of the year.

1. My next art workshop is coming up. Designing Monsters: Ice Age. This one is going to be a collab with Proko. Should be great. Keep an eye out for more info on that because we‚Äôre going live with it very very soon..like today or tomorrow. Sign-ups will take place on Proko.com so watch for the link in my stories.

2. I‚Äôm making some pivots with how I manage my private mentorships. If you want to work together you‚Äôll need to be ready to lock-in and give me your best effort. Fill out the application form via the link in my bio if you‚Äôre interested.

3. Sculpture commissions are live. I have finally cracked the case on how to finish these impressionistic warriors and Minotaurs to a degree which I am satisfied with, and I‚Äôve figured out how to get things shipped out to you guys safely. Send me a DM if you‚Äôd like to commission a piece.
